<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   UN: French Soldier Not Killed by Serbs </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1703142194 Paris AFP in English 1401 GMT 17 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1703142194 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Zagreb, March 17 (AFP) -- A French soldier killed in 
the northwestern Bosnian town of Bihac was probably the victim 
of a Moslem sniper, Matthew Nerzig, spokesman for the UN 
Protection Force [UNPROFOR], said here Thursday. 
  "No final conclusion has yet been reached, so I would point 
out that based on our preliminary investigations, it is our 
judgement that the shot that killed Corporal Stephane Dubrulle 
on March 11 did not come from the Bosnian Serb side," Nerzig 
said. 
  "In fact, we do have indications on a preliminary basis that 
the shot does seem to have come from the Bosnian Moslem side." 
  Dubrulle was the 19th French soldier killed in 
Bosnia-Herzegovina since the beginning of the war. A total of 
79 UN peacekeepers have died in the 23-month war. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

