<F P=100> YUGOSLAVIA </F>
<F P=101> Serbia </F>
<H3> <TI>   New Government, Prime Minister Elected </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1803003294 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 0001 GMT 18 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1803003294 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Belgrade, 17 Mar (TANJUG) -- The Serbian Parliament 
this evening elected a new republican government with Mirko 
Marjanovic as prime minister. Of the 224 deputies present, 128 
voted for Marjanovic's cabinet, 77 were against, and 30 
abstained. The government was elected in a public vote after a 
debate lasting three days in which 135 deputies took part. The 
new Serbian Government consists of the prime minister, five 
deputy prime ministers, 20 department ministers, and four 
ministers without portfolio. 

</TEXT>

