<F P=100> YUGOSLAVIA </F>
<F P=101> Kosovo </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ethnic Albanian Leader Welcomes Federation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1803115894 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1056 GMT 18 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1803115894 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pristina, 18 Mar (TANJUG) -- Ibrahim Rugova, 
president of the Democratic Alliance of Kosovo [Demokratski 
Savez Kosova, DSK], today welcomed the signing of the agreement 
on the Muslim-Croat federation in Bosnia-Herzegovina. 
  At a news conference Rugova described the agreement as the 
first step toward containing the situation and a peaceful 
resolution of the conflict, at the same time warning that 
developments will be more difficult on the ground [than in the 
negotiations] due to war wounds. 
  According to him the question is whether similar things will 
happen in other parts of the former Yugoslavia, since, as he 
said, it [former Yugoslavia] should first be reorganized 
according to ethnic and political criteria. Rugova said 
different and new ways of [implementing] the agreement could not 
be ruled out. He voiced his party's position whereby first of 
all each one [each nation] should be a master in its own home, 
and then economic and other associations will be possible. 
  The DSK president expressed satisfaction with the outcome of 
the discussion on Kosovo in the Belgian Parliament, in 
particular with Belgian Foreign Minister Willy Claes's speech, 
in which, according to Rugova, he had said that Kosovo Albanians 
were now no longer satisfied with the Yugoslav Constitution of 
1974 [that gave them the status of an autonomous province within 
Serbia]. The DSK leader interpreted this as a sign of support 
for the [ethnic] Albanian demand for an independent and neutral 
Kosovo. 
  Rugova welcomed recent demonstrations of Albanians in 
European cities and confirmed that the organizers were the DSK 
and other Albanian associations. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

