<F P=100> SLOVAKIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   National Council Approves Privatization Bill </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1803123594 Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network in Czech 1100 
GMT 18 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1803123594 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Czech </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] The session of the National Council of Slovakia 
continues in Bratislava. Our correspondent Renata Havranova, 
editor of the PRACE daily, has details of this morning's 
deliberations. 
  [Havranova] The Slovak parliament has again debated and 
passed the bill on privatization. After the fiasco suffered by 
Prime Minister Vladimir Meciar when the parliament refused his 
idea of personal union of the government and the National 
Property Fund, Meciar had the law returned by the president to 
the parliament. However, the deputies confirmed the original 
decision, according to which the prime minister cannot hold the 
post of chairman of the presidium of the National Property Fund 
and the finance minister cannot hold the post of chairman of the 
fund's control board. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

