<F P=100> ROMANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ukrainian Defense Minister Arrives on Visit </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1503204494 Bucharest Radio Romania Network in Romanian 
1800 GMT 15 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1503204494 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest Radio Romania Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Romanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Talks between the military delegation led by Army 
General Vitaliy Radeskyy, Ukrainian minister of defense, and 
Gheorghe Tinca, Romanian minister of national defense, 
accompanied by other prominent figures of the Romanian Army 
leadership, took place today in Bucharest. The talks emphasized 
the mutual determination to consolidate ties between the armies 
of the two countries and focused on various ways and means to 
expand cooperation on many planes. The Ukrainian minister 
expressed the desire to extend the military contacts at various 
echelons in order to achieve a better mutual understanding, to 
consolidate the relations of good neighborliness, and to 
positively solve problems of mutual interest. 
  At the end of the visit paid to our country by the Ukrainian 
military delegation, a cooperation accord between the Ministry 
of National Defense of Romania and the Ministry of Defense of 
Ukraine will be signed -- a communique received from the Army's 
press bureau reads. 

</TEXT>

