<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Czech Republic </F>
<H3> <TI>   Klaus Considers Slovakia `Primary Partner' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1703173294 Prague CTK in English 1538 GMT 17 Mar 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1703173294 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Prague, March 17 (CTK) -- The Civic Democratic 
Party (ODS) does not in the least feel entitled to discuss the 
composition of the new Slovak Government, Czech Prime Minister 
and ODS Chairman Vaclav Klaus told journalists today. 
  He said the ODS fully respected Slovakia's sovereignty and 
independence and its new cabinet. 
  The Czech Republic considers Slovakia to be its primary 
partner and has an eminent interest in "smooth, good, and 
constructive relations with the Slovak Government," Klaus said. 
  He warned against the Czech Republic perceiving Slovakia as 
so- called "near abroad." Klaus explained that this term is 
appearing in the interpretation of Russia's politics which makes 
no difference between domestic affairs and foreign affairs. 
"They have invented the term "near abroad" in reference to 
former republics of the former Soviet Union which Russia seeks 
to treat differently than other foreign countries," Klaus 
elaborated. 

</TEXT>

