<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Czech Republic </F>
<H3> <TI>   Zlenko, Zieleniec Initial Treaty </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1703152994 Prague CTK in English 1358 GMT 17 Mar 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1703152994 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Prague, March 17 (CTK) -- The Czech and Ukrainian 
Foreign Ministers Josef Zieleniec and Anatoliy Zlenko initialed 
today a Treaty on Friendship and Cooperation between their 
countries. Zlenko ends today a two-day official visit to the 
Czech Republic. 
  At a press conference the two politicians appreciated the 
importance of the document which is yet to be affirmed on a 
higher level. The Treaty, as well as a Czech-Russian agreement 
on trade and economic relations and an agreement on scientific 
cooperation will be an inspiration for mutual relations. 
  Zlenko said that Czech-Ukrainian economic relations should 
be 
developed, as there existed still unexploited possibilities in 
this sphere. Ukraine will gladly draw from Czech experience 
from the transformation process, Zlenko said. 
  Zieleniec informed Zlenko that Ukraine was one of the Czech 
Republic's significant priorities. Stable Ukraine is also an 
important factor of stabilization in Central and Eastern Europe, 
he added. 
  Zieleniec said he was pleased by Zlenko's confirmation of 
continuing supplies of oil and gas via the Ukrainian territory, 
saying he was glad that the Ukrainian Government saw this 
question as an important part of Czech-Ukrainian relations. The 
two ministers also discussed sub-regional and regional 
cooperation and ways of ensuring security in Europe. 
  Zlenko also met with Czech Premier Vaclav Klaus. After the 
meeting, Klaus said that the Czech Republic was ready to send 
its economic experts to Ukraine if asked to. Zlenko said that 
Klaus had expressed his support for Ukrainian foreign political 
activities. 

</TEXT>

