<H3> <TI>   Cabinet Approves Support for Libya Sanctions </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1703085894 Prague CTK in English 2134 GMT 16 Mar 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1703085894 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Prague, March 16 (CTK) -- At its session today, the 
Czech government approved a bill on the Czech Republic's 
measures aimed against Libya, which would enable the Czech 
Republic to implement the UN Security Council's tightened 
sanctions against Libya, a government spokeswoman told CTK. 
  The UN sanctions against Libya have been in effect since 
December 1, 1993. The Security Council approved them on 
November 11, as Tripoli did not meet its demand to hand over two 
Libyan citizens accused of participation in the explosion of a 
U.S. aircraft over the Scottish town of Lockerbie in 1988, in 
which 270 people lost their lives. 

</TEXT>

