<F P=101> Czech Republic </F>
<H3> <TI>   Former Communist Sees Zhirinovskiy as `Victim' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1603194894 Prague CTK in English 1618 GMT 16 Mar 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1603194894 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Prague, March 16 (CTK) -- Vladimir Zhirinovskiy, 
should he visit the Czech Republic, should be treated at least 
like the Germans "who caused the death of 325,000 people during 
Nazi occupation of Czechoslovakia and are visiting the Czech 
Republic unpunished," former Communist Party high-ranking 
official Miroslav Stepan said today. 
  Stepan, who is currently chairman of the People's Union of 
National and Social Salvation (LUNSZ), told journalists he 
considered it absurd for a "person from a friendly Slav country 
to come here with the handicap of being followed." He said that 
as LUNSZ chairman and as a Czech citizen he would watch 
Zhirinovskiy's views with interest and would "read between the 
lines." 
  Jan Vik, spokesman of the Assembly for the 
Republic-Czechoslovak Republican Party (SPR-RSC) which invited 
Zhirinovskiy to visit the Czech Republic, said today that no 
matter whether the visit took place in several days or later it 
would be very welcomed. Zhirinovskiy is a Russian 
ultra-nationalist and chairman of the Liberal Democratic Party 
(LDP) which emerged victorious in the Russian parliamentary 
elections recently. 
  Stepan said that Zhirinovskiy had become a victim of an 
international information conspiracy. He said that a period of 
strengthening of pan-Slavic solidarity is approaching, so that 
"300 million Slavs not to find themselves in the position of 
nations subservient to overlord nations," the latter being the 
"advanced" states. 

</TEXT>

