<H3> <TI>   SPR-RSC Defends Zhirinovskiy </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1703091094 Prague CTK in English 2220 GMT 16 Mar 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1703091094 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Prague, March 16 (CTK) -- The Assembly for the 
Republic-Czechoslovak Republican Party (SPR-RSC) sees the 
statement by Jan Ruml concerning Vladimir Zhirinovskiy's planned 
visit to the Czech Republic as "an attack against the last 
remains of the democratic paint in our country". 
  During his south Moravian trip on Tuesday [15 March], Ruml, 
the Czech Interior Minister, said he intended to take all 
possible steps to prevent Zhirinovskiy, the leader of Russia's 
Liberal Democratic Party, from staying in the Czech Republic. 
He said he would push his intention through with the use of the 
law on foreigners' stay in the country. 
  A SPR-RSC statement given by a party spokesman to CTK today, 
says the SPR-RSC assures the government that Zhirinovskiy's 
visit to the Czech Republic will take place sooner or later. 
  "Ruml is not disturbed by the crowds of economic refugees 
from the world flowing to the Czech Republic and being nourished 
from our citizens' taxes. Ruml is not disturbed by foreign 
mafias' staying (in the country) and pursuing criminal 
activities...," the statement says. 
  It adds that Ruml is not even disturbed by trips of Sudeten 
German spokesman Franz Neubauer to the Czech Republic, towards 
which he is raising blatant claims. 
  "Not the stance of Vladimir Zhirinovskiy but that of Ruml 
can 
be called fascist, and it directly contravenes the proclaimed 
democracy and post-November (1989) ideas". 
  Vladimir Zhirinovskiy said in Warsaw on March 14 that he 
would pay a visit to the Czech Republic on March 20-21. He has 
been invited by the extreme-right SPR-RSC. 

</TEXT>

