<H3> <TI>   Presidency Rejects Accusations Against Pancea </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1603204494 Bucharest ROMPRES in English 1804 GMT 16 Mar 94 
-- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1603204494 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest ROMPRES </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bucharest, ROMPRES, 16/3/1994 -- "The espionage 
accusations brought against Lieutenant General Marin Pancea and 
carried by some Romanian publications over the past few days are 
pure concoctions and fabrications. Utterly groundless and 
fanciful correlations are being made with certain changes in the 
executive structures of the Romanian Intelligence Service (SRI). 
The president of Romania cannot possibly be thought as due to 
react to such irresponsible absurdities, as it is rather the 
duty of those who launch them to substantiate their allegations 
with evidence and not by unproved assertions," says a press 
release from the presidential spokesman. 
  "The decree of the president of Romania ruling the 
discharging from the position of secretary of Romania's Supreme 
Defense Council of Lieutenant General Marin Pancea and his 
transfer to the reserve was signed and sent for publication to 
the official gazette. The signing of this decree has nothing to 
do with the recent speculations in the press, his transfer to 
the reserve corps having been decided a longer time ago," the 
press release runs. 

</TEXT>

