<F P=101> Yugoslavia, Federal </F>
<H3> <TI>   Minister Rules Out CSCE Visit to Kosovo </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1703100694 Tirana ATA in English 0931 GMT 17 Mar 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1703100694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tirana, March 17 (ATA) -- "The Yugoslav Government 
will not allow the return of the permanent CSCE mission unless 
Yugoslavia will be an equal member of this organization," Margit 
Savovic, acting minister for human rights and minorities 
questions of the so-called Federal Yugoslav Republic declared at 
a press conference. The declaration followed a CSCE request for 
the installation of CSCE missions in Kosova, Sandjak and 
Vojvodina. It added that "Yugoslavia cannot allow to be a 
subject to carry out decisions which it has not approved. It 
doesn't mean that special missions are not allowed to come, but 
on the condition that it must be stressed that they are coming 
to Yugoslavia and not to Kosova, Vojvodina or Sandjak." 
  Ms. Savovic said that they also do not accept the proposal 
of 
an independent Swedish foundation that a civil UN administration 
be installed in Kosova due to human rights violations in the 
territory. She considered this act as "an attempt to 
internationalize the Kosova question and to impose a UN 
protectorate on Yugoslavia". 

</TEXT>

