<F P=100> ALBANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Berisha Hails B-H Agreement, Clinton's Role </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1903204094 Tirana TVSH Television Network in Albanian 1900 
GMT 19 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1903204094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana TVSH Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Albanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Albanian President Sali Berisha has sent a 
greetings telegram to Croatian President Franjo Tudjman and 
Bosnia-Herzegovina President Alia Izetbegovic on the agreement 
to create a confederation which has been signed in Washington. 
Berisha stressed the importance of this agreement in achieving 
a fair peace in Bosnia-Herzegovina, which gives broader hope to 
the region. 
  In a telegram sent to U.S. President Bill Clinton, Berisha 
expressed his high assessment for the very important role of 
President Clinton and the U.S. Government in achieving this 
agreement as well as his conviction on Washington's further 
commitment to resolve the crisis in our region. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

