<F P=100> ALBANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   FYROM's Andonov Requests Use of Port, Fuel </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1803212894 Tirana TVSH Television Network in Albanian 1900 
GMT 18 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1803212894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana TVSH Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Albanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bashkim Kopliku, deputy chairman of the Council of 
Ministers, and his Macedonian counterpart Jovan Andonov held 
business talks in Tirana today. The talks focused on the 
cooperation and port facilities that Albania may offer to 
Macedonia [The Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia -- FYROM] 
on the transport of goods from the Adriatic shores to Macedonia. 
  We are predisposed to help Macedonia, Kopliku said at this 
meeting. Moreover, we are related to Macedonia by the fact that 
about 40 percent of its inhabitants are of Albanian nationality. 
  The talks mainly focused on two main directions of the 
demands by the Macedonian side: to ensure the use of Durres 
port for transport as well as the use of one of the fuel stores 
in Vlore. 
  Assessing the help that Albania would give to Macedonia, 
Macedonian Deputy Prime Minister Andonov asked that 30 percent 
of goods destined for Macedonia should pass through Albania, 
with advantageous conditions regarding customs expenses. 
Kopliku declared the readiness of the Albanian Government to 
reach an understanding. 
  The Macedonian side confirmed its readiness to include 
Albania in the project to construct a gas pipeline from Russia 
to Skopje, and from there to Albania. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

