<F P=100> BULGARIAZ </F>
<H3> <TI>   Romanian `Homegrown Nationalists' Claiming Land </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1803192894 Sofia 24 CHASA in Bulgarian 13 Mar 94 p 6 </F>
<F P=103> AU1803192894 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia 24 CHASA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Bulgarian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed editorial: "Hands Off Dobrudzha!"] </F>
  [Text] Illegal and unrecognized organizations are pouring 
out threats and sharpening their shears regarding Bulgaria, 
while the Romanian leaders simply stay mum when the issue of 
these actions by their homegrown nationalists is raised. 
  To put it mildly, the top statesmen in Bucharest are 
protecting them and say nothing when they reveal their appetites 
for "the ancient Romanian lands." 
  The "Great Romania" Organization has itself admitted in a 
letter that it is acting under the authorities' wing. Again, 
Prime Minister Vacaroiu is reported to have told the parliament 
speaker not to provide any information about the "Romanian 
Guard." 
  The nationalism game in the Balkans has reaped enough 
victims 
this century. It is time for the people in Bucharest to 
remember that we are living in a powder keg, so they should 
refrain from making territorial claims. 
  Alternatively, they should proclaim their claims openly, 
instead of hiding behind real or fictitious organizations. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

