<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Croatian, Bosnian Officials Sign Agreements </TI></H3>
<H4>   Granic Meets With Silajdzic 19 Mar </H4>
<F P=102> LD1903234594 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
2300 GMT 19 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1903234594 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Mate Granic, Croatian deputy prime minister and 
foreign minister, had a meeting with Bosnian Prime Minister 
Haris Silajdzic in Washington today. They discussed the 
implementation of the agreements signed so far and established 
with satisfaction that events were developing in a positive 
direction. For example, prisoners have already been exchanged. 
They stressed that both the Muslim and Croat sides should 
prevent all attempts at provocations. Granic and Silajdzic also 
discussed the strategy of negotiating with the Serb side and 
some current issues, such as the EU's future assistance to 
Croatia and Bosnia-Herzegovina. 

</TEXT>

