<H3> <TI>   Nordic Battalion Soldiers Safe </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1803171694 Paris AFP in English 1706 GMT 18 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1803171694 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tuzla, Bosnia-Herzegovina, March (AFP) -- An 
armoured vehicle of the United Nations Nordic battalion was 
destroyed Friday by shell and heavy machine gun fire near 
Gradacac in northern Bosnia, UNPROFOR spokeman Anders Person 
announced. Person told AFP that the nine soldiers in the vehicle 
were safe, adding: "We don't know who shot at the vehicle." 
Twenty heavy tanks were sent to the scene and NATO planes flew 
overhead as a "power demonstration," Person said. 

</TEXT>

