Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Sarajevo, March 19 (AFP) -- Three people were 
wounded in a mortar attack on Sarajevo Saturday, the press 
service of the Moslem-dominated Bosnian government said, but the 
UN said the blast was caused by a grenade. 
  If the mortar attack were confirmed, it would be the first 
serious breach of a NATO-imposed heavy weapons exclusion zone 
around the capital. But the United Nations Protection Force 
quickly denied that a mortar shell had been fired, blaming the 
blast on a grenade. [passage omitted] 

