<H3> <TI>   TANJUG on UN Response </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1903214494 Belgrade TANJUG in English 2132 GMT 19 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1903214494 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Belgrade, March 19 (TANJUG) -- A U.N. officer has 
resolutely denied allegations by Moslem authorities in Sarajevo 
that the explosion that left three persons wounded in the 
Alipasino Polje suburb on Saturday was caused by a Serb mortar 
shell. 
  Lieutenant-Colonel [name indistinct] Pernod of the French 
battalion within the U.N. Protection Force in war-torn 
Bosnia-Herzegovina said that the explosion was the result of a 
rifle-launched grenade, the AFP reports. 
  The maximum range of such a grenade is 600 metres and the 
nearest Serb positions are 1,500 metres away from the place 
where the explosion occurred, Pernod specified. 

</TEXT>

