<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Bihac Offensive Continues; Many Casualties </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2003100194 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 0900 GMT 20 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2003100194 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The enemy offensive against the area of Bihac is 
continuing unabated. Last night and this morning the Serb 
aggressors opened fire on all defense lines in the Bihac part of 
the battlefield and on the Grmusa-Srbljani plateau. Several 
defenders were killed in the bestial shelling. Karadzic's 
terrorists intensified combat actions in the Bihac region zone 
of responsibility of the Croatian Defense Council, particularly 
in the [name indistinct] part of the battlefield, where they 
tried to infiltrate commando units. The units were routed in an 
energetic action by our fighters, but unfortunately several of 
them were killed in the fighting. 
  Actions by joint forces of the paramilitary formations of 
the 
Kladusa autonomy and chetniks from the so-called Krajina 
continued last night. Using 120-mm mortars, mountain artillery 
pieces and antiaircraft weapons they continued destroying the 
area of Cazin, and the villages of Skrivaja, Viskovac and 
Hatici. A large number of defenders and civilians, who are 
still fleeing this area from Fikret's demented blood-thirsty 
phalanges, were killed in this round of fighting. 
  Also last night, Karadzic's terrorists, using howitzers and 
mortars, shelled Bihac, Cazin, and their suburbs. Two people 
were seriously wounded; eight others suffered only minor 
injuries. Fresh material destruction is considerable. 

</TEXT>

