<F P=102>  LD2003152494 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1400 GMT 20 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2003152494 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] [Announcer] Hajrudin Redzovic reports from the 
Seven-South operational group. 
  [Redzovic] For the first time in the past two years of the 
aggression against our country, the Serb aggressor (?is 
withdrawing) from the operational area of the Seven-South 
operational group [of the Bosnia-Herzegovina Army], which has 
recently come under fierce Serb attacks. [Words indistinct] the 
Bosnia-Herzegovina Army's Third Corps, the Croatian Defense 
Council's 111th Zepce Brigade and the command of the Seventh 
South operative group to hand over and liberate the temporarily 
occupied areas from the Bosna River to Mount Crni Vrh and 
further on, the enemy has withdrawn a large part of its forces 
from Novi Seher, Brankovici, Berkovici, Globarica and other 
villages. 
  The aggressors have withdrawn their forces -- two brigades, 
15 tanks, 50 artillery pieces and other military equipment -- 
from villages that have been occupied for nine months. However, 
chetniks still hold some parts of the occupied territories. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

