<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Serbs Lift Blockade of Enclaves </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1903174194 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
1600 GMT 19 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1903174194 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The blockade of the besieged town of Maglaj and the 
Croatian community of Usora [northeast Bosnia] was lifted at 
1500 today. 
  According to Colonel Ivo Lozancic, the commander of the 
[Bosnian Croat] 111th Brigade, following an ultimatum issued by 
the 111th Brigade Command, the Srpska army today withdrew all 
their military equipment from their lines near Maglaj and the 
roads to Zepce and Usora. They have already reached the 
vicinity of Teslic. The Usora-94 operation was thus 
successfully completed. After several months of blockade the 
Croatian community of Usora is at last linked to the Croats of 
Zepce. 

</TEXT>

