<H3> <TI>   Minister Views Foreign Relations Issues </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2003163394 Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 1600 GMT 20 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2003163394 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 1600 GMT 20 Mar 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Slovak </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The change of government in Slovakia has evoked a 
positive response abroad, Eduard Kukan, the new foreign 
minister, said in the "Kroky" TV program. 
  Regarding relations with neighboring countries, he said that 
he is not very optimistic about whether it will be possible for 
the government to comprehensively resolve relations with the 
Czech Republic and Hungary during its six months in office. A 
peaceful atmosphere, however, must be created first of all. 
  As to the U.S. press, he noted that it views Slovakia as a 
naughty child. That is why it is the role of the new diplomacy 
to provide an objective picture of Slovakia. 

