<H3> <TI>   RSK Prime Minister, Government Resigns </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2003124994 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1232 GMT 20 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2003124994 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Knin, 20 Mar (TANJUG) -- Djordje Bjegovic, prime 
minister of the republic of Serb Krajina (RSK), tendered his 
irrevocable resignation to the position of prime minister at a 
session of Krajina's assembly today. 
  Under the RSK Constitution, the prime minister's resignation 
entails the resignation of the whole government, which will 
however remain in power until a new government is elected. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

