<F P=100> CROATIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   SDSK Rejects Nomination </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1803212694 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1748 GMT 18 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1803212694 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Knin, 18 Mar (TANJUG) -- The Executive Committee 
of the Serb Democratic Party of Krajina [SDSK], chaired by 
former Krajina President Milan Babic, today rejected a proposal 
put forward by Milan Martic, president of the republic of Serb 
Krajina, to appoint Borislav Mikelic as prime minister of the 
new Krajina government, this party announced today. 
  The announcement says that the appointment of Borislav 
Mikelic as the new RSK government's prime minister-designate 
represents an act of ignoring the will of the parliamentary 
majority, which is a constitutional obligation and common 
practice in parliamentary democracies throughout the world. 
  It has also been said that this party was in favor of a 
national unity government, "remaining open to negotiations on 
the composition of the government with all political factors, 
which is in the national interest." [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

