<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   New Political Coalition Founded in Slupsk </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1903213194 Warsaw Third Program Radio Network in Polish 
2100 GMT 19 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1903213194 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw Third Program Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Polish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Representatives of six political groups in 
Slupsk--Solidarity, the Christian-National Union, the Polish 
Democracy Party, the Movement for the Republic, Center Accord, 
and the Polish Peasant Party-Peasant Accord--have created an 
electoral bloc under the name "Christian-Independence Forum." 
The alliance is opting for the development of local 
self-governments and is expressing itself in favor of the 
decentralization of the state. 

</TEXT>

