<H3> <TI>   Zhelev Supports Elections, `Probably in Fall' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1803175594 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network in Bulgarian 1700 
GMT 18 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1803175594 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia Khorizont Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Bulgarian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In a brief interview for the "Around the World and 
at Home" program on Bulgarian National Television, which will be 
transmitted in an hour's time, President Zhelyu Zhelev said that 
he has visited Prime Minister Berov and that the prime 
minister's health continues to improve. This was announced in a 
release from the press center of the Presidency. 
  According to the release, the president said that early 
elections should be held, probably in the fall. 
  In the interview the president supported the demand made by 
the chief editors of 15 central newspapers that press 
publications should not be subject to value-added tax. He 
stressed the responsibility of the media for checking the 
authenticity of the information they disseminated. The 
president specifically mentioned certain insinuations [passage 
indistinct]. 

