<H3> <TI>   `Main Figures' of Draft 1994 Budget Published </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2103093694 Tirana GAZETA SHQIPTARE in Albanian 20 Mar 94 p 
3 </F>

<F P=103> AU2103093694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana GAZETA SHQIPTARE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Albanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Where the Budget Will Go -- Defense </F>
Privileged"] 
  [Text] Tirana -- Here are some of the main figures in a 
breakdown of the state budget for 1994. The data are taken from 
the Budget Bill just submitted to parliament. It is evident 
that the largest funds of more than 6 billion leks go to the 
Education Ministry. Most of this, or 4.4 billion leks, will go 
for local funding and only 500 million will be used for national 
funding. The Health Ministry comes second, with funds amounting 
to more than 4.9 billion leks. Two other ministries, those of 
construction and defense, are financed to the tune of more than 
4 billion leks. The state budget also gives priority to the 
Public Order Ministry and the Ministry of Labor and Social 
Welfare, both of which receive more than 2 billion leks. Of a 
total budget of 74.140 billion leks, more than 63.927 billion 
leks will be used for central funding. More than 13.551 billion 
leks of the budget will be used as investment finance. 


