<F P=100> ROMANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry Hails Bosnia-Croatia Accords </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1803185894 Bucharest Radio Romania Network in Romanian 
1800 GMT 18 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1803185894 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest Radio Romania Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Romanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A fax sent to us by the Romanian Ministry of Foreign 
Affairs announces that it greets with satisfaction the signing 
in Washington of the accord on the creation of a bicommunity 
federation by the Bosnian Muslims and Bosnian Croats and of the 
accord on the principles of a possible confederation between 
Bosnia-Herzegovina and Croatia. 
  The Romanian Ministry of Foreign Affairs believes that the 
signing of these documents represents an important step toward 
decisively involving all sides in the continuation and 
finalization of the negotiations aimed at a global settlement of 
the Yugoslav crisis. 
  Emphasizing the decisive contribution made by the United 
States to the achievement of these accords, the Ministry of 
Foreign Affairs assesses that, through the sustained efforts by 
the international community, one can achieve viable and 
realistic understandings that will contribute to solving a 
large-scale conflict in the heart of Europe by political means, 
a conflict that causes tremendous human suffering and great 
material damage. 
  The communique reaffirms the Romanian Government's complete 
readiness to contribute, through its means, to supporting the 
current positive processes of reestablishing peace and settling 
problems in keeping with the major interests of the newly 
emerged states on the territory of former Yugoslavia and of 
their neighboring countries in the interests of security and 
peace. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

