<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   NATO, Serb Leaders Hold Talks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2203132694 Paris AFP in English 1244 GMT 22 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2203132694 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Sarajevo, March 22 (AFP) -- UN officials and Bosnian 
Serb military leaders have agreed to settle amicably the 
controversial discovery of heavy weapons inside the NATO-imposed 
exclusion zone around Sarajevo, a UN spokesman said Tuesday [22 
March]. 
  Major Simon MacDowall, spokesman for the UN Protection Force 
(UNPROFOR), said the weapons -- tanks, anti-aircraft guns and 
mortars -- were discovered Sunday by Canadian troops in the 
village of Cifluk right at the edge of the 20-kilometre 
(12-mile) exclusion zone set by NATO. 
  He said the weapons were placed under UN control even though 
the Serbs consider Cifluk outside the exclusion zone. 
  The Serbs have defined the exclusion zone by using 
Sarajevo's 
cathedral as the central point from which to calculate the 20 
kilometres while the UN defines the centre about a kilometre 
further west from the cathedral. 
  Bosnian Serb leader Radovan Karadzic and UNPROFOR chief of 
staff in Bosnia, Dutch General Adrian van Ball, held a meeting 
in the Serb stronghold of Pale Monday and agreed to negotiate 
the controversy. "Van Ball came back very satisfied with the 
positive attitude of the Bosnian Serbs," MacDowell said. He said 
the exclusion zone could not be entirely monitored by UN 
peacekeepers because of a lack of manpower. He added, however, 
that the situation had been relatively calm since NATO issued an 
ultimatum February 9 threatening air strikes unless the Serbs 
and Bosnian government troops withdrew their heavy weapons from 
around the besieged capital. He said UN military observers had 
noticed that troops on both sides appeared more relaxed on the 
frontlines and there was "no more sniping in Sarajevo." "That 
forward momentum is still going on," he said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

