<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Attacks Detailed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2103152194 Belgrade TANJUG in English 1455 GMT 21 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2103152194 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["Pool" item] </F>
  [Text] Kupres, March 21 (TANJUG)--Moslem forces from 
Bugojno (central Bosnia) continued attacks on Serb positions at 
the Kupres plateau for six days now, using infantry and 
artillery, local Serb military sources said on Monday. In 
these battles, one combatant of the Bosnian Serb Army was 
killed, and two others were lightly wounded. 
  The Kupres plateau is militarily very important, because 
strategically important roads go from the Adriatic coast towards 
central and western Bosnia via this plateau. 
  The issued statement says Serb defenders have so far 
re-gained about 80 percent of the territory which Moslem 
extremists from Bugojno seized few days ago. The Moslem forces 
on Monday attacked the Serb positions between Cajnice, Foca and 
Gorazde (southeast Bosnia) but all attacks have been repelled 
with no losses among the Serb troops, these sources said on 
Monday. 
  The Moslems continued attempting infiltrating terrorist and 
sabotage groups behind the Serb lines. One such group was 
detected Sunday afternoon in the area between Cajnice and 
Gorazde and their attempt was thwarted on time. Another 
terrorist and sabotage group suffered the same fate near Teslic 
(northern Bosnia). 
  In the wider region of Doboj (northern Bosnia), the Moslem 
forces continued with usual provocations. The strongest 
provocations by the Moslem forces were reported near Mt Ozren, 
whereas re-grouping of Moslem forces was observed in the valleys 
of the Rivers Bosna and Spreca. 

</TEXT>

