<F P=100> SLOVAKIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Denies `Liquidation' of REPUBLIKA </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2103151794 Bratislava REPUBLIKA in Slovak 18 Mar 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> AU2103151794 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava REPUBLIKA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Slovak </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Interview with Prime Minister Jozef Moravcik by "zl" on 16 </F>
March in Bratislava: "Does the Government Have the Means or 
Not?"--in the "Hot Questions For" column] 
  [Text] After the first meeting of the government on 
Wednesday [16 March], we asked the Slovak prime minister: 
  [REPUBLIKA] REPUBLIKA is the only daily that is inconvenient 
for the government. Has the government adopted measures to 
liquidate this daily? 
  [Moravcik] The government does not have the means to 
liquidate dailies. Or does it? The press ought to be 
independent, also economically. I believe that it can fulfill 
its role only when it is independent. 
  [REPUBLIKA] In other words, you have not dealt with the 
liquidation of REPUBLIKA in the government? 
  [Moravcik] No, not yet. 

</TEXT>

