<F P=100> CZECH REPUBLIC </F>
<H3> <TI>   Labor Minister Barred From Addressing Rally </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2203130894 Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network in Czech 1200 
GMT 22 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2203130894 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Czech </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] The Prague rally staged by the Czech-Moravian 
Chamber of Trade Unions Association [CMCTUA] is about to end. 
Our correspondent Jiri Bohacek reports: 
  [Bohacek] Pavel Hajek, CMCTUA deputy chairman, addressed the 
rally at noon. The Old Town Square was 75-percent full. Labor 
and Social Affairs Minister Jindrich Vodicka arrived at that 
time, but the trade unionist crowd would not allow Vodicka to 
join them. The speakers asked those present to make room so 
that Mr. Minister could leave. Minister Vodicka was forced to 
leave without being allowed to speak or defend himself. 
According to unconfirmed information, a member of Mr. 
Minister's entourage was injured. [passage omitted] 
  Distributors of leaflets published by the Association for 
the 
Republic appeared among the participants at the rally, but they 
failed to hand out any of their literature. 
  It seems that the rally has just ended. The gathering sang 
the anthem and people are leaving. 

</TEXT>

