<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   Holds Discussion With Olechowski </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2103175194 Warsaw PAP in Polish 1715 GMT 21 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2103175194 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Polish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, 21 Mar--Issues of European security and the 
international situation were the main topics of talks held today 
by the foreign ministers of Poland and Ukraine, Andrzej 
Olechowski and Anatoliy Zlenko. The talks, scheduled for half 
an hour, lasted twice that long. 
  Plenary talks between both delegations began after the 
ministers' meeting. These talks focus on bilateral political 
and economic relations. At the outset of the talks, Minister 
Zlenko said that Poland and Ukraine are two great neighbors who 
might play an important role in the region. 

