<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Hungary </F>
<H3> <TI>   Boross, Jeszenszky Greet New Slovak Government </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2103174494 Budapest MTI in English 1405 GMT 21 Mar 94 -- 
FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2103174494 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest MTI </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Budapest, 21 Mar (MTI) -- Prime Minister Peter 
Boross has sent a telegram of greetings to newly appointed 
Slovak Prime Minister Jozef Moravcik, wishing him success and 
expressing his satisfaction with Moravcik's statement, which 
took a stand for settling Hungarian-Slovak relations as soon as 
possible. "I believe good intentions on both sides will help us 
solve current problems and that the Hungarian and Slovak peoples 
will join their creative powers to tackle their common 
historical tasks," Boross wrote. 
  Foreign Minister Geza Jeszenszky sent his congratulations to 
his Slovak counterpart Eduard Kukan. Jeszenszky wrote he 
believed that improving Hungarian-Slovak links was considered to 
be a priority by the Slovak foreign minister, too. 

</TEXT>

