<H3> <TI>   Romanian Ship Held After Violating UN Embargo </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1803184294 Budapest MTI in English 1747 GMT 18 Mar 94 -- 
FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1803184294 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest MTI </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Budapest, 18 March (MTI) -- A Romanian river 
freighter was held up at Mohacs on the south Hungarian stretch 
of the Danube due to its violation of UN sanctions against rump 
Yugoslavia, local customs authorities told MTI. 
  The ship, Slobozia Mare, arrived at Mohacs on Monday [14 
March] with Budapest as its destination. When checked 
thoroughly for compliance of embargo regulations, it was found 
to be carrying only 18 tonnes of oil instead of the 52 tonnes 
indicated in its official documents, with water replacing the 
missing quantity. 
  According to unconfirmed information, the Romanian captain 
and the crew of two Serbs and six Ukrainians admitted to having 
sold the missing oil, worth 2.7 million forints ($1 equals 103 
forints), in Serbia. Customs investigations are continuing. 

</TEXT>

