  [Text] Budapest, 21 Mar (MTI) -- The new Slovak 
Government's aim is to improve its country's general image, 
requiring higher standards in politics, Slovak Defence Minister 
Pavol Kanis told a press conference after meeting his Hungarian 
host and counterpart Lajos Fur in Budapest today. Kanis said 
Slovakia hoped for better ties with Hungary, between the two 
countries and also the two ministries. 
  "Our talks covered regional security, bilateral military 
cooperation, NATO's peace partnership programme, and cooperation 
between the Visegrad countries," the Slovak minister said. 
  Fur saw the new Slovak foreign policy as promising, citing 
