Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Bratislava, March 18 (CTK) -- [passage omitted] 
The new privatization minister, Milan Janicina, speaks about the 
problem of feverish privatization [by the outgoing government of 
Vladimir Meciar in its last days in office] in an interview with 
today's edition of the independent SME newspaper. He claims 
many projects were incomplete and their approval therefore was 
against the law. 
  Commenting on the suspicion that Meciar destroyed certain 
documents before vacating his chair as acting head of the 
Privatization Ministry, Janicina says that neither Meciar nor 
his state secretary Ivan Lexa gave him an agenda, and he even 
had to borrow a secretary so someone could make him coffee. 
  Janicina intends to propose that the new government rescind 
the former government's resolution on the approval of 
privatization projects. He said there were no plans as yet to 
replace ministry staff. What was important was the staff "are 
able and have clean hands," he said. 

