<H3> <TI>   Ethnic Hungarians To Cooperate With Government </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2103094394 Prague CTK in English 1841 GMT 20 Mar 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2103094394 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bratislava, March 20 (CTK) -- "We were not too 
enthusiastic about the (Slovak ethnic) Hungarian parties not 
being taken into account when the new government was composed," 
Arpad Duka-Zolyomi, deputy chairman of the ethnic Hungarian 
party Egyutteles (Coexistence), said in a televised debate today. 
  However, he said his party was willing to cooperate with the 
new government despite the Hungarian parties not being members 
of the government coalition. The previous cabinet of Vladimir 
Meciar rejected any dialogue, he added. 
  Zolyomi said he agreed that the ethnic Hungarian parties 
held 
the balance of power in the Slovak parliament. 
  Premier Jozef Moravcik said that the coalition parties 
expected the above mentioned cooperation. A hierarchy of 
problems solvable before early elections, to be held at the end 
of September and beginning of October, has been created, 
Moravcik added. 

</TEXT>

