<H3> <TI>   Official Says SNS To Act as Opposition </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2103094494 Prague CTK in English 1951 GMT 20 Mar 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2103094494 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bratislava, March 20 (CTK) -- The behavior of the 
Slovak National Party (SNS) will be fully oppositional, similar 
to that of the behavior of the former opposition, the chairman 
of the SNS parliamentary group of deputies, Miloslav Kona, told 
Slovak television today. 
  He stressed that the SNS would react to all steps taken by 
the government. "The SNS is waiting for signals by the 
government and then we will response," he noted. 
  Kona said he was convinced that Slovakia's ethnic Hungarian 
parties, with which the new cabinet wants to cooperate, did not 
contribute to a calm atmosphere on the Slovak political scene. 
  Before the early elections scheduled for autumn, the SNS 
intends to focus on attitudes of the Hungarian parties and 
reactions to them. "The SNS finds it very interesting that it is 
the Hungarian parties which hold the balance of power in 
Parliament," Kona said. 

</TEXT>

