<F P=101> Yugoslavia, Kosovo </F>
<H3> <TI>   Construction Sites Given to Serb Settlers </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1803161794 Tirana ATA in English 1124 GMT 18 Mar 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1803161794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tirana, March 18 (ATA) -- As the result of 
Albanians' transfer from Kosova due to Serbian persecution and 
violence, new Serbian population centres are being formed in 
Prishtina. 
  According to a decision of the Serbian leaders of the 
Prishtina commune, 50 construction sites will be given to 
Serbians who will be settled in Kosova. The sites are located 
in the "Dragogan" Quarter in Prishtina. The place is sufficient 
to provide residence for 15,000 inhabitants, that is the same 
number of Serbians are expected to live in this area. 
  In this context, 150 houses are foreseen to be constructed 
near the Technical Faculty while 100 construction sites will be 
granted at the "Tasligje" Quarter. All the sites will be given 
to Serbians free of charge. The sale of the construction sites 
is prohibited, leaving no possibilities for the Albanians to buy 
them. 
  Such undertakings of colonization have existed before in 
Kosova and will also continue in the future in other Kosova 
zones. 

</TEXT>

