<F P=100> BULGARIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Defense Leaders Order Organizational Reforms </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2203092394 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network in Bulgarian 2000 
GMT 21 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2203092394 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia Khorizont Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Bulgarian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A meeting of the Defense Ministry leadership 
reportedly took place on 18 March. It was chaired by Defense 
Minister Valentin Aleksandrov and attended by deputy ministers 
of defense, the chief of the General Staff and his deputies, and 
the commanders of the Armed Forces branches. 
  The elimination of duplicating units in the Ministry of 
Defense system was one of the items on the agenda discussed at 
the meeting. 
  In this connection the minister of defense ordered that his 
personal chancery and the general chancery of the Ministry of 
Defense should be closed down. A chancery of the Ministry of 
Defense was established instead. Colonel Engineer Konstantin 
Seizov was appointed chief of the new chancery. He is the 
former chief of the general chancery. 

</TEXT>

